        <num>CCP 5151</num>
        <heading>Section </heading>
        <content>
          <p>CHAPTER 4.  DISCUSSION
Art. 5151.  Discussion defined
Discussion is the right of a secondary obligor to compel the creditor to enforce the obligation against the property of the primary obligor or, if the obligation is a legal or judicial mortgage, against other property affected thereby, before enforcing it against the property of the secondary obligor.</p>
        </content>
